<h1><font color="#5C8526">Milestone:Informal Statement</font></h1>
<ul><li><h2>Informal statement of the problem</h2></li>
<li><h2>A multimedia database for dogs is R1(ID, NAME, PHOTO, TYPE) where ID is the primary key. This database R1 can be searched by TYPE. The SQL query Q1 is:</h2></li>
<li><h2>select *</h2></li>
<li><h2>from R1</h2></li>
<li><h2>where type == “pugs”</h2></li>
<li><h2>A new multimedia dependency is introduced: PHOTO --&gt; TYPE so that we can now search by matching photos of different dogs.</h2></li>
<li><h2>Problem 1 : Describe the transformation algorithm in psuedocode and show how the database R1 can be systematically transformed into a normalized database R2.</h2></li>
<li><h2>Problem 2 : Describe the transformation algorithm in pseudocode and show how the query Q1 can be systematically transformed into a new query Q2.</h2></li>
</ul></body>
